        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: support Azure Responses text stream events",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nCompanion/follow-up to #88893 for #88833. This branch addresses the code/test blockers called out on #88893 and the later Azure Foundry runtime findings on this PR.\n\nChanges:\n- accept Azure Responses `text` content parts alongside OpenAI `output_text` in the shared parser;\n- handle Azure `response.text.delta` in both parser paths;\n- stream documented `response.output_text.delta` into Azure `text` content parts;\n- update `src/agents/openai-transport-stream.ts` so the active Azure Responses transport path uses the same stream compatibility behavior;\n- use the regular OpenAI-compatible SDK client for non-traditional Azure `/openai/v1` Responses endpoints such as Azure AI Foundry project URLs, avoiding the AzureOpenAI SDK `api-version` query injection;\n- keep traditional `*.openai.azure.com` and `*.cognitiveservices.azure.com` hosts on `AzureOpenAI` with `api-version`;\n- add explicit `type: \"message\"` plus array `input_text` content for system/developer/user Responses input messages in both converter paths;\n- keep the SDK client/request seam typed to SDK `ResponseStreamEvent` and widen only the parser input to a narrow Azure-compatible event union;\n- make streaming tests feed one continuous event sequence through `processResponsesStream`; and\n- add coverage for Azure text deltas emitted without a preceding `response.content_part.added` event.\n\n## Validation\n\nRun locally on Windows with pnpm 11.2.2:\n\n```text\nnpm exec --yes pnpm@11.2.2 -- test -- src/llm/providers/openai-responses-shared.test.ts src/llm/providers/azure-openai-responses.test.ts src/agents/openai-transport-stream.test.ts\nnpm exec --yes pnpm@11.2.2 -- tsgo:core\nnpm exec --yes pnpm@11.2.2 -- tsgo:test:src\n```\n\nFocused test result:\n- `src/llm/providers/openai-responses-shared.test.ts`: 11 passed\n- `src/llm/providers/azure-openai-responses.test.ts`: 3 passed\n- `src/agents/openai-transport-stream.test.ts`: 231 passed\n\n## Live proof status\n\nPigfoot provided isolated Azure AI Foundry proof in https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/89001#issuecomment-4591888658 after applying two local runtime fixes. This PR now includes those runtime fixes:\n- Foundry/OpenAI-compatible `/openai/v1` client selection without injected `api-version`;\n- explicit `type: \"message\"` on Responses input messages.\n\nTheir reported canaries after those fixes:\n- no-tools Foundry canary final text: `AZURE_RESPONSES_CANARY_OK`, `fallbackUsed = false`;\n- tool-continuation Foundry canary final text: `AZURE_RESPONSES_TOOL_CANARY_OK`, one tool call, zero tool failures, `fallbackUsed = false`.\n\n## Related\n\n- #88893\n- #84109\n- Fixes #88833 if maintainers accept this as the canonical landing branch.",
